:%s/(k\zs\(.\{-}\)\ze,/\=setreg("A", submatch(1), 'V')/n
# %s subsitution
# / start matching 
# \zs start match highlight (\zs can only used in search mode)
# \{-} is non-greedy match, replace *
# \ze end match highlight
# \=setreg call setreg function
# "A", set to register A
# submatch match group select 
# 'V' linewise mode
# /n dry run, not subsitute.
qaq
# clear register
# q recording
# a record to register a
# q end recording
"ap
# paste content in register a 

# show invisible char
:set list
# Use \< and \> for word start and word end, respectively.
/\<Glip
